  protein: 17 g
  sodium: 2 g
servings: 2
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 45 minutes
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Remove the core from the @red pepper{2} and @yellow pepper{1} and @green pepper{1} and cut into 1cm wide slices. Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and chop into ½cm chunks (or as small as you can). Roughly chop the @coriander{1/2%bunch} leaves, discarding the stalks. Lastly, drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%400g can} in a #colander{} or #sieve{}.

Coat your peppers in a splash of @olive oil{1%splash} and a good pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Place on a #baking tray{} and put on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{20%minutes}, or until they're soft and a little crispy around the edges.

Heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a #non-stick frying pan{} over medium heat. When hot, add your onion and cook for ~{5%minutes} before adding in the mixed beans, @habanero sauce{1/4%cup}, @ground cumin{1%tsp}, @tomato puree{1%tsp} and the @water{100%ml}. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{}.

> Tip: Add as much habanero sauce as you can handle - be careful, it's hot!

Cook with a #lid{} on for ~{15%minutes} until thickened and starting to break down.

Grate a pinch of @lime{1/2}(zested), squeeze a dash of lime juice and add a sprinkle of salt and black pepper into the @sour cream{1/2%cup}. Give it all a good stir and keep to one side.

Now to make your refried beans! Remove one-third of your bean mixture to a #bowl{}. Mash the rest to a paste in the pan using the back of a #fork{} or a #potato masher{}. Now add your reserved beans back into your mashed beans along with half of your coriander. Taste and add some salt if necessary.

Put the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} in your oven for ~{2%minutes} to warm. Toss the @wild rocket{40%g} in a little leftover lime juice, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%drizzle} and a good pinch of salt and pepper.

We like to serve the peppers, chilli bean mix and citrus sour cream in separate bowls so everyone can dive in. Alternatively, you can add the ingredients to your tortillas, roll them up in the kitchen and send them out to the camp fire! Don't forget an extra dollop of your citrus sour cream, your dressed rocket and a final sprinkle of coriander!